1
00:00:14,667 --> 00:00:16,167
I already called dad.

2
00:00:16,467 --> 00:00:18,833
I told him to tighten
the security.

3
00:00:19,133 --> 00:00:21,300
I also told him about
what you saw.

4
00:00:21,433 --> 00:00:22,867
He told the police already.

5
00:00:23,100 --> 00:00:28,300
As long as Mom Rina's at large,
I can't have peace of my mind.

6
00:00:28,433 --> 00:00:30,767
My mom can't harm us anymore.

7
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:32,367
She can't find us here.

8
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:33,733
I wonder what she meant
when she said

9
00:00:33,900 --> 00:00:34,867
she have a surprise.

10
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:38,233
Congratulations, son.

11
00:00:38,367 --> 00:00:43,267
Even if your mom is not here,
I hope you are happy.

12
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:44,433
Thanks, Dad.

13
00:00:46,367 --> 00:00:50,133
I can't miss this opportunity
to send my regards.

14
00:00:50,267 --> 00:00:54,767
This video message is perfect
for you.

15
00:00:54,900 --> 00:00:57,900
Because you won't be able
to handle

16
00:00:58,033 --> 00:01:02,167
my advance wedding gift for you.

17
00:01:03,133 --> 00:01:05,133
Are you ready?

18
00:01:05,267 --> 00:01:08,400
Your baby is not dead.

19
00:01:08,567 --> 00:01:10,000
Yes, you heard me right.

20
00:01:10,133 --> 00:01:11,867
Your child is not dead.

21
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:16,400
In fact, she's very much alive.

22
00:01:16,533 --> 00:01:20,100
We have to get her back, Red.
We have to get our baby back.

23
00:01:20,233 --> 00:01:22,100
There's only one person who can
confirm

24
00:01:22,233 --> 00:01:24,600
if Rina's telling the truth.

25
00:01:24,733 --> 00:01:27,300
And that's if he's going
to talk.

26
00:01:28,333 --> 00:01:31,467
Red, what if Uncle Zandro won't
tell us the truth?

27
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:35,100
You know he doesn't care
about us, right?

28
00:01:35,233 --> 00:01:38,400
I think he will take
Mom Rina's side until the end.

29
00:01:39,367 --> 00:01:40,800
I'm really sorry, Yen.

30
00:01:40,967 --> 00:01:43,600
It's not our fault. We only
got caught in between.

31
00:01:43,733 --> 00:01:48,100
No matter what happens,
I don't regret loving you.

32
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:49,600
What's going on?

33
00:01:49,733 --> 00:01:51,700
Are you now one big happy
family?

34
00:01:51,833 --> 00:01:53,967
You came to visit me
empty-handed.

35
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:55,733
Red, come on.

36
00:01:55,867 --> 00:01:57,867
We need something from you.

37
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,167
From me?

38
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:01,000
Tell us the truth.

39
00:02:01,133 --> 00:02:03,033
Is our child alive?

40
00:02:03,167 --> 00:02:04,633
You should ask Rina.

41
00:02:04,767 --> 00:02:07,000
Because wherever
your child is...

42
00:02:07,133 --> 00:02:11,300
whether she's dead or alive,
in heaven or hell...

43
00:02:11,433 --> 00:02:13,033
I don't care!

44
00:02:13,167 --> 00:02:15,533
Have pity on us. And our baby.

45
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:17,133
You know we have
nothing to do with this.

46
00:02:17,267 --> 00:02:20,333
We just got caught in between
their feud.

47
00:02:20,467 --> 00:02:22,967
What will I gain
from helping you?

48
00:02:23,100 --> 00:02:24,600
You are out there having
the time of your life.

49
00:02:24,733 --> 00:02:26,800
While I'm rotting in jail.

50
00:02:26,933 --> 00:02:30,100
Zandro, we'll help you
with your case.

51
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:36,000
The midwife that helped you
give birth works for us.

52
00:02:36,133 --> 00:02:43,000
We switched your baby
with a dead newborn.

53
00:02:43,133 --> 00:02:45,700
That was the baby you buried
and cried for.

54
00:02:46,733 --> 00:02:50,567
So that means our baby's
still alive?

55
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:59,033
So my child is still alive?

56
00:03:09,733 --> 00:03:11,667
You know what to do with that,
right?

57
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,067
Yes.

58
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:15,333
I'll switch this baby
with a dead one.

59
00:03:15,467 --> 00:03:18,400
I don't want to see
that child ever again.

60
00:03:18,533 --> 00:03:20,867
Thelma, make sure
you don't mess up.

61
00:03:21,033 --> 00:03:22,233
I don't want any trouble.

62
00:03:22,367 --> 00:03:23,467
Don't worry.

63
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:26,400
I have a lot of contacts
where I can sell this child.

64
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:33,500
Our baby is still alive, Red!

65
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:35,733
I knew it.

66
00:03:37,567 --> 00:03:38,533
Mom...

67
00:03:38,667 --> 00:03:40,667
Yen, I'm sorry.

68
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:44,067
I'm sorry that I convinced you
to move on.

69
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:47,067
I thought our
baby was gone.

70
00:03:47,633 --> 00:03:50,633
I didn't even have an intuition
that she was alive.

71
00:03:52,733 --> 00:03:53,767
It's not your fault, Red.

72
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,600
It's not our fault.

73
00:03:55,767 --> 00:03:57,567
We don't deserve this.

74
00:03:59,733 --> 00:04:03,800
Where's our baby, Uncle Zandro?
I want to be with her.

75
00:04:03,933 --> 00:04:05,633
Please, tell us where she is.

76
00:05:03,533 --> 00:05:06,100
Zandro...

77
00:05:13,533 --> 00:05:14,800
Yes!

78
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:18,633
My brother.

79
00:05:21,233 --> 00:05:23,867
I wonder how Chloe's doing.

80
00:05:24,967 --> 00:05:26,233
What is she eating?

81
00:05:26,367 --> 00:05:28,633
What kind of milk
are they giving her?

82
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:32,933
We've been away from her
for several months now.

83
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,967
What if she's sick?

84
00:05:37,033 --> 00:05:39,633
I'm sure she's just like you.

85
00:05:39,900 --> 00:05:42,233
She's tough and strong like you.

86
00:05:42,367 --> 00:05:43,600
Mom.

87
00:05:43,733 --> 00:05:44,800
What's the matter?

88
00:05:44,933 --> 00:05:46,600
I'm trying to encourage you.

89
00:05:46,733 --> 00:05:49,467
Why are you scaring yourself?

90
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:54,600
What matters is that we can now
get your baby back.

91
00:05:54,733 --> 00:05:56,900
She will be with you.

92
00:05:58,767 --> 00:06:01,167
I don't know how my mom
could do this.

93
00:06:02,133 --> 00:06:02,967
I'm her son.

94
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:06,000
How can she hurt me like this?

95
00:06:06,133 --> 00:06:07,300
Red.

96
00:06:07,467 --> 00:06:09,967
She tried to ruin our family.

97
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:11,467
We wouldn't find out that
our child is alive

98
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,300
if she didn't get imprisoned.

99
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:17,233
Rina needs to go back to jail.

100
00:06:18,033 --> 00:06:21,167
We must find her once we have
proof that your baby is alive.

101
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:25,567
She needs to pay for her crime.

102
00:06:26,367 --> 00:06:30,000
I don't think it will be
that easy, Lucho.

103
00:06:30,133 --> 00:06:31,733
Rina has a plan.

104
00:06:31,867 --> 00:06:35,300
She has a reason she told us
about the baby.

105
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:38,500
I hope I'm wrong.

106
00:06:38,833 --> 00:06:40,600
But I don't think it
will be easy for us

107
00:06:40,767 --> 00:06:42,267
to get your child back.

108
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:55,133
You really thought
of everything.

109
00:07:17,300 --> 00:07:23,267
But since you're in jail,
I will use this for now.

110
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:48,233
This will be an explosive
surprise!

111
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,600
What are we doing here, Red?

112
00:08:18,733 --> 00:08:22,133
We should find our baby.

113
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:23,567
Yen, I want to find her too.

114
00:08:24,733 --> 00:08:27,933
But we have to make sure
that it's safe.

115
00:08:28,067 --> 00:08:29,567
That she didn't lay down a trap.

116
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:30,367
Okay?

117
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:31,933
Dad will take care
of everything.

118
00:08:32,067 --> 00:08:34,000
He will contact the police.

119
00:08:36,267 --> 00:08:37,967
You have to rest for now.

120
00:08:39,067 --> 00:08:41,033
Do you want anything?
Do you need water?

121
00:08:59,067 --> 00:09:00,333
Oh my god!

122
00:09:02,133 --> 00:09:03,433
Oh my god!

123
00:09:03,567 --> 00:09:05,367
Your water broke!

124
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:07,933
You're in labor, Eden!

125
00:09:08,067 --> 00:09:09,967
Zandro!

126
00:09:10,100 --> 00:09:11,267
It hurts!

127
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:13,000
- I can't bear it anymore!
- We're almost there, Eden.

128
00:09:13,133 --> 00:09:13,967
Hold on.

129
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:15,967
Do something, Zandro!

130
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:18,833
- Do something about this!
- I will!

131
00:09:20,833 --> 00:09:21,700
One more.

132
00:09:21,833 --> 00:09:23,933
- There it is!
- Push, push! Come on!

133
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:28,600
Yes.

134
00:09:33,833 --> 00:09:35,667
Eden, your baby's gone.

135
00:09:39,333 --> 00:09:44,167
She's gone.

136
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:48,000
Only one person can do this.

137
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,533
It's Amanda.

138
00:09:52,033 --> 00:09:53,867
What kind of joke is this?

139
00:09:55,533 --> 00:09:58,800
This is painful for all of us.

140
00:09:58,933 --> 00:10:03,533
But if it's up to me,
I want Amanda to pay for this.

141
00:10:03,700 --> 00:10:04,867
She needs to go back to jail.

142
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,000
Serves her right.

143
00:10:06,133 --> 00:10:07,167
She has to go back to jail.

144
00:10:07,300 --> 00:10:09,600
Look at what she's been doing
to our family!

145
00:10:09,733 --> 00:10:11,200
- Auntie.
- What, Eden?

146
00:10:11,333 --> 00:10:14,600
What? Are you going to defend
your mom again?

147
00:10:14,733 --> 00:10:18,167
Isn't what she did to us enough?

148
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:22,067
Mom, I lost my baby!

149
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:25,900
I didn't even get to cuddle her
or kiss her.

150
00:10:26,033 --> 00:10:29,200
I didn't even get
to hold her, Mom!

151
00:10:29,333 --> 00:10:30,167
Sorry.

152
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:32,033
Sorry?

153
00:10:32,167 --> 00:10:35,733
Can it bring my baby back?

154
00:10:35,900 --> 00:10:38,933
Please, Mom,
just leave me alone!

155
00:10:39,067 --> 00:10:41,900
Let me go!

156
00:10:49,867 --> 00:10:51,633
I'll get you something to drink.

157
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,567
Red, my mom.

158
00:10:58,133 --> 00:10:59,900
My mom...

159
00:11:03,467 --> 00:11:04,967
Yenyen?

160
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:08,033
I've noticed how anxious
you are.

161
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,367
Here.

162
00:11:09,633 --> 00:11:11,067
Drink some water.

163
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:23,533
Mom...

164
00:11:24,433 --> 00:11:27,067
Mom, I've hurt you a lot.

165
00:11:31,133 --> 00:11:33,233
- No, Eden.
- I hated you before

166
00:11:33,367 --> 00:11:38,833
because I believed you were
the reason my baby died.

167
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:45,733
I even swear that I would never
forgive you.

168
00:11:47,333 --> 00:11:48,967
That's all in the past now.

169
00:11:49,100 --> 00:11:50,600
No, Mom.

170
00:11:50,833 --> 00:11:52,733
I've been such a horrible
daughter.

171
00:11:54,233 --> 00:11:56,500
That's not true.

172
00:11:57,500 --> 00:12:00,567
That's probably why baby Chloe's
been taken from us.

173
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:02,567
It's what I deserve.

174
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:05,033
I'm a bad daughter.
Mom, I'm sorry.

175
00:12:07,100 --> 00:12:11,933
That's what Rina made you
believe, so you'd hate me.

176
00:12:14,467 --> 00:12:16,467
And she succeeded.

177
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:20,467
She brainwashed me, Mom.

178
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:22,800
It shouldn't have happened.

179
00:12:22,933 --> 00:12:23,833
I should know.

180
00:12:23,967 --> 00:12:26,433
I should know you well
as my mom.

181
00:12:26,567 --> 00:12:28,633
I should know that you love me.

182
00:12:28,767 --> 00:12:31,800
But I believed Mama Rina.

183
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:34,000
I should have known.

184
00:12:34,133 --> 00:12:38,167
I should have known you
couldn't do that to me.

185
00:12:38,300 --> 00:12:39,900
I'm sorry.

186
00:12:43,633 --> 00:12:45,567
I made a lot of mistakes too.

187
00:12:45,700 --> 00:12:48,000
I did you and Red wrong things.

188
00:12:49,833 --> 00:12:59,033
And it allowed Rina to ruin
our relationship.

189
00:12:59,167 --> 00:13:02,433
No, Mom. I'm so sorry.

190
00:13:02,567 --> 00:13:04,667
I'm sorry, Mom.

191
00:13:06,467 --> 00:13:08,133
I'm sorry.

192
00:13:09,333 --> 00:13:10,833
I'm sorry too.

193
00:13:12,733 --> 00:13:15,933
I'm sorry for all the times
I hurt you.

194
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,467
I'm sorry, Eden.

195
00:13:26,733 --> 00:13:32,600
We know the truth now.
And that's all that matters.

196
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:37,033
We will get your baby back.

197
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:42,833
And our family will be complete.

198
00:13:45,100 --> 00:13:46,400
Eden...

199
00:13:50,033 --> 00:13:53,367
No one can get
in between us anymore.

200
00:13:55,300 --> 00:13:57,267
I promise you.

201
00:13:59,833 --> 00:14:00,700
Mom.

202
00:14:03,333 --> 00:14:04,167
I'm sorry.

203
00:14:04,300 --> 00:14:06,000
I love you so much, dear.

204
00:14:06,133 --> 00:14:08,267
I love you too, Mom.

205
00:14:25,300 --> 00:14:28,467
We've already identified
the midwife named Thelma Joven.

206
00:14:28,733 --> 00:14:30,900
Rina Ramos' brother confirmed
that she's the midwife

207
00:14:31,033 --> 00:14:33,600
that worked for them.

208
00:14:33,733 --> 00:14:36,733
But we don't know what happened
to the child.

209
00:14:36,867 --> 00:14:38,800
Rina probably took the child.

210
00:14:38,933 --> 00:14:40,900
She's the one you
should look for.

211
00:14:41,033 --> 00:14:42,967
We couldn't trace
her movements.

212
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:46,900
So let us know if you hear
from her.

213
00:14:47,033 --> 00:14:49,233
If she texts or calls you.

214
00:14:52,033 --> 00:14:54,600
You can rely on our cooperation.

215
00:14:54,733 --> 00:14:56,500
So you can put Rina back in
jail.

216
00:14:56,633 --> 00:14:59,567
I don't want my wife
to hurt anybody else.

217
00:14:59,700 --> 00:15:01,167
Thank you, Sir.

218
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:02,533
We'll get going.

219
00:15:22,133 --> 00:15:25,400
Red, this is not the place
where they took me.

220
00:15:26,733 --> 00:15:28,233
I asked around.

221
00:15:28,367 --> 00:15:30,667
They said Thelma's always
moving.

222
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:32,200
This is where she lives now.

223
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:49,667
Yen!

224
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:53,467
Mom!

225
00:16:10,933 --> 00:16:12,800
Our baby's not here.

226
00:16:13,767 --> 00:16:15,467
Where's my baby?

227
00:16:28,067 --> 00:16:29,667
Rina got her first.

228
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:33,467
Mom, where's my baby?

229
00:16:43,433 --> 00:16:44,733
Bam!

230
00:17:13,133 --> 00:17:15,567
Lord, please.

231
00:17:15,867 --> 00:17:17,567
I'm begging you.

232
00:17:18,867 --> 00:17:21,400
Please, watch over my child.

233
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:26,133
I know you're protecting her
while she's not with me.

234
00:17:27,967 --> 00:17:33,233
I pray that you'll give her
back to me.

235
00:17:35,433 --> 00:17:37,500
I want to hold her.

236
00:17:38,833 --> 00:17:41,033
I want to hug my child.

237
00:17:43,067 --> 00:17:44,467
Please, keep her safe.

238
00:17:45,933 --> 00:17:48,700
Don't allow any harm befall her,
Lord.

239
00:17:51,100 --> 00:17:52,600
Please.

240
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:02,900
Yen.

241
00:18:03,700 --> 00:18:05,700
The police officers are here.

242
00:18:08,333 --> 00:18:10,267
Red, I'm scared.

243
00:18:11,367 --> 00:18:16,133
I don't know what Mom Rina
can do to our child.

244
00:18:17,167 --> 00:18:18,833
Yen.

245
00:18:20,667 --> 00:18:22,467
Red, she could hurt baby Chloe.

246
00:18:22,633 --> 00:18:25,567
She could kill her
just to get revenge.

247
00:18:25,833 --> 00:18:27,767
Yen, don't think like that.

248
00:18:27,900 --> 00:18:30,500
How can I stop myself
from thinking like this?

249
00:18:30,633 --> 00:18:33,233
Look at what's happening to us.

250
00:18:35,567 --> 00:18:38,467
Red, I want to stay hopeful.

251
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:40,700
But it seems so hard.

252
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:42,000
I know.

253
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:46,033
But let's not give up.

254
00:18:46,167 --> 00:18:47,967
Yen, for our child's sake.

255
00:18:49,233 --> 00:18:51,100
For baby Chloe.

256
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:58,067
Yen, I promise you.

257
00:18:59,267 --> 00:19:01,833
We'll find her.
We'll get her back.

258
00:19:04,467 --> 00:19:07,533
We will all wake up
from this nightmare.

259
00:19:09,300 --> 00:19:11,033
I promise.

260
00:19:23,333 --> 00:19:25,800
What are we going to do now?

261
00:19:26,133 --> 00:19:27,867
Do you know a place where
she could be hiding?

262
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:31,233
Sir Victor, do you have
a vacation house

263
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:33,567
or a place Rina frequents?

264
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:36,700
I'm sure she will avoid
all those places.

265
00:19:37,867 --> 00:19:39,400
What are we going to do?

266
00:19:39,533 --> 00:19:41,167
Are we just going
to sit here?

267
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:47,767
Hello?

268
00:19:48,133 --> 00:19:49,467
Hello?

269
00:19:49,833 --> 00:19:50,933
It's Mom.

270
00:19:55,233 --> 00:19:56,867
Hello?

271
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:58,700
Can you hear me?

272
00:19:58,833 --> 00:20:00,867
Mom, where's our baby?

273
00:20:07,133 --> 00:20:08,433
Where did you bring our baby?

274
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:10,600
Relax, Red.

275
00:20:11,033 --> 00:20:12,667
Don't get too excited.

276
00:20:13,133 --> 00:20:13,933
My baby!

277
00:20:14,067 --> 00:20:16,000
Don't hurt our baby!

278
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:19,700
Rina, leave the child out
of this!

279
00:20:20,367 --> 00:20:21,067
Who is that?

280
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:22,800
Is that Amanda? Amanda?

281
00:20:23,233 --> 00:20:25,467
Amanda, hello!

282
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:27,900
Don't hurt our baby!

283
00:20:28,233 --> 00:20:31,433
Well, you know it's all up
to you, Eden.

284
00:20:33,833 --> 00:20:36,667
I won't hurt your baby if...

285
00:20:37,033 --> 00:20:39,067
you do everything I say.

286
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:41,367
I'll give you everything
you want!

287
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:44,867
Just don't hurt our baby.
Give her back!

288
00:20:45,267 --> 00:20:46,500
Anything I want?

289
00:20:47,467 --> 00:20:49,700
That's what you said.

290
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:51,700
You will give me everything
I want.

291
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:53,200
You'll do everything.

292
00:20:53,333 --> 00:20:54,567
Fine.

293
00:20:55,600 --> 00:21:00,267
I will give your baby back if...

294
00:21:04,033 --> 00:21:08,067
you give me your mother.

295
00:21:09,133 --> 00:21:13,567
Give me Amanda in exchange
for your daughter.

296
00:21:13,700 --> 00:21:14,933
Deal?

297
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:22,000
You're out of your mind!

298
00:21:22,133 --> 00:21:25,567
You must be crazy to think
I'll give you my wife!

299
00:21:25,700 --> 00:21:26,167
No!

300
00:21:26,300 --> 00:21:27,400
Oh, shut up, Lucho!

301
00:21:27,533 --> 00:21:29,733
I have got the upper hand
right now

302
00:21:29,867 --> 00:21:34,967
because I have something
very valuable to you.

303
00:21:35,100 --> 00:21:36,400
Mom.

304
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:38,867
Mom, please.

305
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:43,833
Please, give us our baby back.

306
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,733
Don't you care about me anymore?

307
00:21:45,867 --> 00:21:47,433
Is that why you're doing this
to me?

308
00:21:47,567 --> 00:21:49,067
You too, Red!

309
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:52,767
Didn't you abandon me too?

310
00:21:52,900 --> 00:21:56,600
You made me feel I'm worthless
to you!

311
00:21:56,733 --> 00:21:57,333
Rina!

312
00:21:57,467 --> 00:21:59,500
Rina, you have to surrender.

313
00:21:59,733 --> 00:22:00,667
We'll help you.

314
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:01,767
I'll help you.

315
00:22:02,067 --> 00:22:02,800
You, too!
You're a liar!

316
00:22:03,933 --> 00:22:05,500
You abandoned me too.

317
00:22:05,833 --> 00:22:08,833
You will all feel my wrath!

318
00:22:12,133 --> 00:22:14,933
Enough of this drama, please.
Okay?

319
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:20,867
Bring Amanda to me in exchange
of this baby.

320
00:22:22,067 --> 00:22:24,567
And don't you ever call
the police.

321
00:22:24,700 --> 00:22:26,200
I will find out if you did.

322
00:22:27,967 --> 00:22:30,900
You will get into more trouble.

323
00:22:31,300 --> 00:22:41,000
So, bring Amanda here
to Zandro's hideout at 6 pm.

324
00:22:41,533 --> 00:22:45,200
Baby and I will be waiting.

325
00:22:45,333 --> 00:22:47,700
Please, leave the baby out
of this!

326
00:22:51,733 --> 00:22:54,133
Right, baby?

327
00:22:57,833 --> 00:22:59,200
Shut up!

328
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:02,467
Our baby, Red.

329
00:23:12,133 --> 00:23:15,233
Our visitors are here, baby.

330
00:23:15,367 --> 00:23:16,567
Chloe.

331
00:23:16,700 --> 00:23:19,100
Don't you dare come here!

332
00:23:19,233 --> 00:23:20,433
You're not who I want!

333
00:23:20,567 --> 00:23:22,333
Give me Amanda,

334
00:23:22,500 --> 00:23:25,000
or else you will never see
your child again!

335
00:23:25,133 --> 00:23:27,367
I love Amanda so much, Dindi.

336
00:23:27,500 --> 00:23:29,767
I still can't believe
she's my wife now.

337
00:23:29,900 --> 00:23:34,400
So I'll do everything
to defend her.

338
00:23:34,533 --> 00:23:35,867
To protect her.

339
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,833
I'm here now.
I'll come with you.

340
00:23:37,967 --> 00:23:38,900
No, Mom!

341
00:23:39,033 --> 00:23:41,700
- Stay out of this, Eden!
- Mom, Mom, please!

342
00:23:41,833 --> 00:23:44,567
We have a deal, remember?
That's why I'm here.
